for Restructuring the Economic Systems, is heading a delegation 
to have an in-depth investigation into Australia's economic and 
financial structures. 
  During his trip, which will also bring him to Canberra and 
Sydney, Li will meet government ministers as well as industrial 
and financial leaders. 
  It is understood that these meetings will focus mainly on 
bilateral economic relations and Australia's economic and fiscal 
polices. 
  He will also make speeches at the Australia-China Business 
Council and the Asia-Australia Institute, briefing them on 
China's on-going economic and financial reforms and its foreign 
investment policy. 

