<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qiao Shi Meets With Indian Communist Party Visitors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qiao Shi Meets With Indian Communist Party Visitors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2006142894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1409 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2006142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 20 (XINHUA) -- A senior leader of the 
Chinese Communist Party (CPC) said here today that the party 
hopes to further its ties with the Communist Party of India 
(Marxist). 
  Qiao Shi, member of the Standing Committee of the Political 
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, said that the party values 
the active role of the Indian party in the maintenance and 
promotion of the friendly ties between the two countries and the 
two peoples. 
  The CPC is willing to further its links with the Communist 
Party of India (Marxist) on the four inter-party principles of 
independence, equality, mutual respect and non-interference in 
each other's internal affairs, Qiao said. 
  Welcoming Harkishan Singh Surjeet [name as received], 
general 
secretary of the Communist Party of India (Marxist), Qiao also 
conveyed to him the best regards of Jiang Zemin, general 
secretary of the CPC Central Committee. 
  China and India are not only neighbors but also among the 
biggest developing countries in Asia, Qiao said, adding that in 
recent years, the two countries have witnessed smooth growth of 
bilateral ties and strengthened cooperation in international 
affairs. 
  The strengthening of their cooperation in various fields is 
in line with the interests of the two nations, and is conducive 
to peace, stability and development in Asia and the world as a 
whole, said Qiao, who is chairman of the Standing Committee of 
China's National People's Congress. 
  Surjeet told Qiao that his visit is aimed at knowing more 
about China's policy of reform and opening to the world, its 
achievements as well as its problems. 
  "We are deeply impressed by the great achievements China has 
obtained in recent years," he said. 
  The Communist Party of India (Marxist) speaks highly of Deng 
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics and is confident of socialism's future, he said. 
  Li Shuzheng, head of the International Liaison Department of 
the CPC Central Committee, took part in the meeting. 

</TEXT>

