<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   NPC Vice Chairman Chen Muhua Meets Jordanian Guests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NPC Vice Chairman Chen Muhua Meets Jordanian Guests </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2206114494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1109 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 22 (XINHUA) -- Chen Muhua, 
vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of China's National 
People's Congress (NPC), met with a Jordanian Government 
delegation here today. 
  Chen, also president of the All-China Women's Federation 
(ACWF), exchanged views with the group on the Fourth World 
Conference on Women to be held here next year and other issues 
of common interest. 
  The delegation, headed by Kamel Abu-Jaber [name as 
received], 
former minister of foreign affairs, senator and member of the 
Senate's Foreign Affairs Committee, arrived here on June 19 upon 
acwf's invitation. 
  After the meeting, Chen hosted a dinner for the delegation. 

</TEXT>

