<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nepalese Premier Inaugurates Beijing-Aided Highway </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nepalese Premier Inaugurates Beijing-Aided Highway </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2206094294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0908 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pokhara, Nepal, June 22 (XINHUA) -- China-aided 
Pokhara-Baglung highway in western Nepal is put into use today. 
  In an inaugural ceremony held in Pokhara, a city of western 
Nepal, this morning, Nepali Prime Minister Girija Prasad Koirala 
extended his appreciation to the economic help given by the 
Chinese Government for construction of the Pokhara-Baglung 
highway. 
  The prime minister said that Nepal would name the new 
highway 
as Thirbarn Malla and Yogandra Man Highway, names of two 
national heroes. 
  During the ceremony, Chinese Ambassador to Nepal Shao 
Jiongchu said that the highway will be another landmark for the 
close cooperation between the two countries and expressed the 
confidence that the newly-constructed highway in western Nepal 
would go a long way in promoting the economic development in the 
western part of the country. 
  The project commenced on April 1, 1988 and completed on 
April 
8, 1994. The highway has a total length of 71.6 kilometers and 
the total investment of about 12 million U.S. dollars. 

</TEXT>

