<F P=102>   OW2206094494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0918 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 22 (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of 
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said here today that China 
attaches great importance to developing friendly ties with the 
Republic of Gabon. 
  Li, meeting with Edmond Nkogho, president of Gabon's 
Economic 
and Social Council (ESC) [name and title as received], and his 
party, said there have always been good relations between China 
and Gabon, and between the CPPCC and ESC. 
  The group's visit will serve to further exchanges between 
the 
two countries in economic, trade and other spheres, Li noted. 
  China, while engaging in large-scale economic construction, 
needs a stable and harmonious domestic situation as well as a 
friendly and peaceful international environment, Li said. 
  Only under these conditions can China focus all its 
attention 
on economic construction and develop exchanges and cooperation 
with other countries, Li said. 
  Nkogho said Gabon desires to further its friendly ties of 
cooperation with China. 
  Speaking highly of China's achievements in reform and 
opening 
to the outside world, Nkogho said that Gabon, which is also 
committed to economic development, is willing to draw on China's 
experience. 
  Nkogho and his party arrived here on June 20 at the CPPCC's 
invitation. 

</TEXT>

