<H3> <TI>   Austrian Chancellor Interviewed on Li Peng's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Austrian Chancellor Interviewed on Li Peng's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2206160494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1519 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206160494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, June 22 (XINHUA) -- Austria welcomes the 
forthcoming official visit by Premier Li Peng, the first by a 
Chinese chief of government, said Chancellor Franz Vranitzky 
here today when interviewed by XINHUA reporters. 
  According to the chancellor bilateral relations have enjoyed 
smooth development since his visit to China last April and he 
stressed that economic cooperation is quite satisfactory. 
  The chancellor said he feels glad that a large economic 
group 
will accompany Premier Li during his European visit. He 
suggested that the two countries have a future of cooperation in 
a variety of economic fields, such as energy, transport and 
sewage disposal, in which Austria has much experience. 
  "The two countries will sign a series of economic accords 
during Li's visit to Austria," he said. 
  He spoke highly of China's socialist market economy and its 
great economic achievements. 
  He stressed that Austria will not limit its attention within 
Europe in spite of its formal EU membership from January 1, 
1995, rather, it will attach more importance to the relationship 
with countries and regions outside the continent. 

</TEXT>

