<H3> <TI>   Czech Trade Show Scheduled for China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Czech Trade Show Scheduled for China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1606144594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1410 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1606144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, June 16 (XINHUA) -- A Czech industrial 
product exhibition, the largest over recent years to be held in 
China, will take place this December in an effort to promote 
economic ties between the two countries. 
  According to reports, the Czech Government believes China's 
huge trade market is so attractive that it will send either its 
Minister of Industry and Trade Vladimir Dlouhy or Economic 
Minister Karel Dyba to attend the opening ceremony. 
  Prague is also planning to earmark 5 million korun (about 
220,000 U.S. dollars) to subsidize enterprises taking part in 
the exhibition, allocating 100,000 korun or some 4,400 dollars 
for each unit. 
  The Czech Republic exported products worth 250 million U.S. 
dollars to China last year, registering a 2.5 times increase 
over the previous two years. 
  They were chiefly machine tools, transport and brewery 
equipment and chemicals. It also imported raw materials, 
foodstuffs, textiles and other industrial products from China. 

</TEXT>

