<H3> <TI>   Estonian President Praises China for Great Achievement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Estonian President Praises China for Great Achievement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2106012494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0101 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2106012494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, June 20 (XINHUA) -- Estonian President 
Lennart Meri, who just came back from a visit to China on Sunday 
[19 June], today praised China for the great achievement it has 
made in reform and opening to the outside world. 
  Speaking at a press conference here, the president said 
China 
is a great country and plays an important role in international 
affairs as a permanent member of the U.N. Security Council. 
  During his stay in China from June 12 to 18, Meri said, he 
held meetings with Chinese leaders, including President Jiang 
Zemin and Premier Li Peng, on bilateral relations and 
cooperation in the political and economic fields. 
  Talking about China's economic achievement, he said Chinese 
economy has been developing rapidly over the past few years, 
adding that the Estonian press has failed to discover these 
great changes in China. 
  The president believed that the two countries have a great 
potential in economic and trade cooperation. 
  As to the issue of Taiwan, Meri reaffirmed that Estonia only 
recognizes one China and will never set up any political link 
with Taiwan. 

</TEXT>

