<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qian Qichen Inspects Guangdong, Comments on SEZs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qian Qichen Inspects Guangdong, Comments on SEZs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2306141394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1407 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2306141394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, June 23 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier 
and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen stressed here that the 
country's coastal areas, particularly the Special Economic Zones 
[SEZs], should push their reform and opening up drive to an even 
higher level. 
  Qian, who is a member of the Political Bureau of the Central 
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), made these 
remarks when he was touring south China's Guangdong Province 
from June 17 to 22. 
  He said during his inspection that the coastal areas, 
particularly the special economic zones, which have been the 
country's pilot areas to carry out the policy of reform and 
opening to the outside world, have strong economic and 
technological forces and have accumulated rich experience in 
international trade, should now concentrate their efforts on 
developing high-tech industries and adopting high-level 
management. 
  Vice-Premier Qian visited Shenzhen and Zhuhai Special 
Economic Zones as well as Zhongshan and Foshan cities. He also 
inspected some ports, airports and tourist resorts. 
  After inspecting several ports linking the mainland of China 
with Hong Kong and Macao, Qian said that customs should be 
strict in making checks and pay attention to providing good 
facilities for trade and exchanges. 
  With the economic development, it was also necessary to 
promote ideological and ethical progress. 
  Vice-Premier Qian also inspected some dikes where local 
people and soldiers were fighting the floods. He conveyed 
regards to the flood fighters on behalf of the CPC Central 
Committee and the State Council. 

</TEXT>

