<H3> <TI>   Jiangxi People's Congress Adopts Variety of Regulations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jiangxi People's Congress Adopts Variety of Regulations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2306063594 Nanchang Jiangxi People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1100 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2306063594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nanchang Jiangxi People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ninth Session of the Eighth Provincial People's 
Congress Standing Committee concluded in Nanchang this 
afternoon. The closing session was presided over by Mao Zhiyong, 
secretary of the provincial party committee and chairman of the 
provincial people's congress standing committee. Standing 
Committee Vice Chairmen Wang Zhaorong, Chen Kuizun, Wang Guoben, 
Wang Zhongfa, and Hu Dongtai attended the session. Huang 
Zhiquan, vice governor of the provincial government, attended 
the session as a nonvoting delegate. Also present at the 
session as nonvoting delagates were persons in charge of the 
provincial higher people's court and the provincial people's 
procuratorate, persons in charge of the various departments of 
the provincial people's congress, and persons in charge of the 
standing committees of the people's congresses of the cities 
under the jurisdiction of the provincial government and liaison 
offices in various prefectures of the standing committee of the 
provincial people's congress. Of the 55 persons who were 
anticipated to attend the session, 48 were present. A quorum 
was thus achieved. 
  The session adopted the "Regulations of Jiangxi Province 
Concerning the Management of River Courses," the "Regulations of 
Jiangxi Province Concerning the Protection of the Citizens' 
Right to Report Offenders," the "Management Regulations of 
Jiangxi Province Concerning the Addition of Iodine to Table Salt 
to Eliminate Iodine Deficiency Hazards," the approval decision 
on the "Provisional Regulations of Nanchang City Concerning the 
Management of the Cultural Market," the approval decision on the 
"Regulations of Nanchang City on the Management of the Labor 
Market," and the list of personnel appointments and removals. 
  Liu Dali, Wang Jiafu, and Yue Dayou, members of the 
provincial people's congress, spoke at the session. 

</TEXT>

