<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiujiang City in Jiangxi Draws Overseas Investment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jiujiang City in Jiangxi Draws Overseas Investment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2306083994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0826 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2306083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nanchang, June 23 (XINHUA) -- Jiujiang, an eastern 
Chinese city with an excellent harbor on the Chang Jiang river, 
has accelerated its infrastructure construction to provide 
better conditions for overseas investment. 
  According to an official from the city, the central 
government and Jiangxi Province are spending over three billion 
yuan on 20 key construction projects in Jiujiang during the 
Seventh Five-Year Plan period (1991-1995). 
  Opened to foreign ships in 1992, Jiujiang harbor has regular 
cargo shipping services to various parts of the world. Its 
airport links the city with Beijing, Nanjing and Huiyang in 
Guangdong Province. New air routes are being planned with 
regular flights to Shanghai, Xiamen, Guangzhou, Shenzhen and 
Haikou. 
  A major bridge across the Chang Jiang river is being built 
in 
the city. Railway lines from Beijing to Kowloon, from Shanghai 
to Chongqing, and from Jiujiang to Hefei, which are all under 
construction, will make the city an important transportation 
center. 
  With a favorable investment environment and promising 
potential, the city approved 144 foreign investment projects 
during last year alone, with an investment of 140 million U.S. 
dollars. 
  To further improve its investment conditions, the city plans 
to invest a total of 10 billion yuan by the end of the century 
in such sectors as communications, telecommunications and energy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

