<H3> <TI>   Shanghai's Outskirts Attract Foreign Investment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai's Outskirts Attract Foreign Investment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2206075594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0725 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206075594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, June 22 (XINHUA) -- The outskirts of 
Shanghai have become a favorable place for overseas investment. 
  Altogether 3,204 enterprises with overseas investment, 
accounting for 46 percent of the city's total, have been set up 
on the outskirts. They involve a sum of 3.04 billion U.S. 
dollars. 
  According to Lu Nanxing, an official of the municipal 
commission of agriculture, 52 percent of these enterprises have 
ties with Hong Kong, 16.2 percent with Taiwan, 11.6 percent with 
the United States and 8.8 percent with Japan. 
  Lu noted that a number of these enterprises have formed 
enterprise groups so as to better compete on the market. 

</TEXT>

