<H3> <TI>   Shanghai To Build Largest Container Base </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai To Build Largest Container Base </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2006030494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0246 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2006030494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, June 20 (XINHUA) -- Shanghai will build 
the country's largest container-shipping base in co-operation 
with a Hong Kong company. 
  Shanghai is China's largest port and its container shipping 
operations have boomed in recent years. 
  The port handled a record 937,000 standard containers last 
year, and the number of containers it handled in the first five 
months of this year was up 40 percent over the same period of 
last year. 
  To meet the needs of the rapid development of container 
transport, the Shanghai Port Comprehensive Container Development 
Corporation is co-operating with Orient Overseas (Holdings) Ltd 
of Hong Kong to develop a 260,000-sq-m area into a container 
shipping base on the outskirts of the city. 

</TEXT>

