<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Henan Secretary Discusses State Enterprises </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Henan Secretary Discusses State Enterprises </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2306072994 Zhengzhou Henan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1030 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2306072994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zhengzhou Henan People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Provincial party committee Secretary Li Changchun 
invited persons in charge of a number of loss-making state-run 
enterprises to a meeting convened in Luoyang on 13 June to 
discuss and map out ways and means of turning enterprise losses 
into profits. 
  Secretary Li Changchun delivered a speech in which he 
emphatically called for firmly grasping each and every excellent 
opportunity at the moment, further emancipating our minds, 
deepening the on-going enterprise reform, and boldly trying out 
a variety of new reform measures. He stated: We should 
strictly implement the spirit of the Third Plenary Session of 
the 14th CPC Central Committee by further developing the 
productive forces; promoting lateral associations between 
enterprises; forming more enterprise groups; correctly handling 
relations between reform and development, on the one hand, and 
stability on the other; carrying out production in light of 
market demand; producing more readily marketable products; 
shifting enterprise operational mechanisms; focusing on heavy 
industrial growth, while continually pushing ahead with light 
and textile industrial growth; and amalgamating more loss-making 
enterprises with profit-making enterprises, with a view to 
turning enterprise losses into profits. To this end, he said, 
all comrades concerned should further enhance a sense of 
enterprise reform and should strive to accelerate the on-going 
enterprise reform. 
  Secretary Li Changchun noted: The large and medium-sized 
state- run enterprises also should implement a joint-stock 
cooperative system on a trial basis, further expand opening up 
to the outside world, and firmly grasp two key work aspects at 
the same time. 

</TEXT>

