<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hunan Flood Control Work, Relief Efforts Underway </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hunan Flood Control Work, Relief Efforts Underway </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Floods in Changsha Receding </H4>

<F P=102> OW2206161794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1549 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Changsha, June 22 (XINHUA) -- The floods which 
besieged this capital of Hunan Province since June 16 were 
finally receded below the warning water level 18:00 hours today. 
  Some 560,000 Armymen and residents have worked days and 
nights to combat the floods for almost a week. 
  The Changsha city government and the city committee of the 
Communist Party of China have now begun to organize manpower to 
help resume production, while continuing operations to fight any 
further possible floods. 
  During the past flood, the highest water level recorded at 
the Changsha monitoring station was 38.93 m [meters], some 3.93 
m above danger level. 
  One hundred and eighteen towns of eight prefectures and 
cities along the Xiangjiang River were flooded. 
  Flood water also entered some 20 streets and lanes of 
Changsha, more than 300,000 city dwellers were affected. Over 
400 factories and 5,000 shops had to stop production or suspend 
business. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

