<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Construction of Large Coal Mine in Guizhou Starts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Construction of Large Coal Mine in Guizhou Starts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2206020494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0110 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206020494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guiyang, June 22 (XINHUA) -- Construction of the 
Jinjia Coal Mine began recently. It belongs to the Panjiang 
Administration of Mines. 
  The mine is designed to produce 1.8 million tons of coal a 
year. It is expected to go into production within five years. 
The cost of creating the mine will reach 500 million yuan (57 
million U.S. dollars). 
  Fan Jinsheng, an official of the Department of Coal 
Production of Guizhou provincial government, said that Jinjia 
Mine, at the junction of the two provinces of Guizhou and Yunnan 
and the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, will help provide 
power and industrial raw materials to a large number of backbone 
enterprises in south-west China. 
  It will thus play an important role in the economic 
development of Guizhou Province and even of the whole south-west 
China area. 
  He said that Guizhou is rich in coal resources. The verified 
reserves of coal deposits amount to 50 billion tons, making the 
province top among the nine provinces and autonomous regions 
south of the Chang Jiang river. 
  The province now produces 45 million tons of coal a year and 
provides a dozen provinces and autonomous regions with coal and 
electricity. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

