<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing To Hold Electronics Industry Trade Fair </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing To Hold Electronics Industry Trade Fair </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2206104194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1025 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 22 (XINHUA) -- Beijing is to hold a 
large electronics products investment and trade fair here June 
28-30 to promote overseas investment in the sector. 
  The city will offer more than 70 investment projects for 
discussion at the fair. The projects include mobile telecom 
equipment, color monitors, satellite television receiving 
systems, optical user terminals and automatic tellers. 
  Wang Dishan, deputy-director of the Electronics Industry 
Office of the Beijing Municipal Government, said that the coming 
fair has received active responses from over 70 international 
companies and agencies in Beijing from about 20 countries and 
regions including the United States, Japan and Canada. 
  A famous brands and high quality electronics products 
exhibition will be held at the same time. The exhibition will 
display more than 100 models of 20 kinds of products. 
  The electronics will be a pillar industry in Beijing. More 
than 80 foreign-funded enterprises have been founded in the 
sector. 
  Wang said that Beijing will offer preferential policies for 
foreign investors. 

</TEXT>

