<H3> <TI>   Tianjin-Seoul Air Route Busy; Flight Added </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tianjin-Seoul Air Route Busy; Flight Added </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2106164294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1517 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2106164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, June 21 (XINHUA) -- More and more 
passengers are flying between north China's port city of Tianjin 
and Seoul, capital of the Republic of Korea (ROK), as economic 
cooperation prospers. 
  Last week, one more flight, a Boeing 737, was added to the 
present seven flights per week between the two cities. 
  Sources at Tianjin airport said that the seat occupancy rate 
reached 80 percent. Tickets to Seoul have been booked to July. 
  The air route is jointly flown by Air China and an air 
company of the ROK. 
  More than 300 Sino-ROK joint ventures have been established 
in Tianjin. 

</TEXT>

