<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Geothermal Field Found in Tianjin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Geothermal Field Found in Tianjin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2106080594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0744 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2106080594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, June 21 (XINHUA) -- A new geothermal field 
of 840 sq m [square meters] has been discovered near this north 
China port city. 
  According to a local energy official, a three-year survey of 
geothermal reserves in the area is well on its way to completion. 
  Geologists say the temperature at the well mouth of the 
"Shanlinzi" geothermal field, which is the second-biggest after 
the Wanglanzhuang field, that has ever discovered in this city, 
is between 75 and 96 degrees centigrade. 
  The amount of heat that can be used is equivalent to that 
given off by 12.23 million tons of standard coal, they claim. 
  The exploration of geothermal resources in this area started 
in the 1970s. To date, some 14 thermal wells have been drilled 
and tap to serve industry, agriculture and animal husbandry, 
tourism and daily life of local people. 
  Tianjin boasts rich geothermal resources, and some ten 
geothermal fields have been found. They cover a total area of 
3,074 sq m and have a total hot water reserve of 7.876 cu m 
[cubic meters]. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-26544 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi121_r_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-121 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Joint Venture Container Firm Set Up in Tianjin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Joint Venture Container Firm Set Up in Tianjin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2206084994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0826 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206084994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, June 22 (XINHUA) -- A new joint venture 
container company has been set up in Tianjin, north China's 
biggest industrial center. 
  The company, co-financed by the Tianjin port and a container 
firm of the Republic of Korea, is the thirtieth joint venture to 
be built in the port. 
  The port now has eight container berths capable of handling 
over one million containers yearly. 
  The container turnover time has been shortened to 21 days 
from the previous 45 days due to a land-and-water coordinated 
transport system with more than 120 inland container relay 
stations built in Baotou, Zhengzhou, Xian, Chengdu, Yinchuan and 
Lanzhou cities. 
  The company has opened over 50 water routes for scheduled 
container shipments to more than 160 countries and regions 
around the world. 

</TEXT>

