<H3> <TI>   Shaanxi Launches Inspection of Audio, Video Tape Market </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shaanxi Launches Inspection of Audio, Video Tape Market </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2206150794 Xian Shaanxi People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
0500 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2206150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Xian Shaanxi People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Provincial Department of Radio and Television, 
the Provincial Department of Culture, the Provincial 
Administration for Industry and Commerce, the Provincial 
Department of Public Security, the Provincial Press and 
Publications Administration, and the Provincial Copyright 
Administration have launched a joint inspection of the audio and 
video tape markets in the Xian area. In audio-visual product 
stores in the Dachengshi section of Beida District, inspectors 
seized 360 pirated cassette tapes, 547 video tapes, 1,390 
compact discs, and 119 laser discs. Some of these audio and 
video products contained indecent material and others were 
poorly produced. During the inspection, inspectors discovered 
that some audio-visual product stores were operating without a 
business license, while others did not have any legitimate 
source of supply. The store operators did not have any 
understanding of copyrights and lacked the ability to tell 
genuine products from counterfeit ones. 
  It has been learned that, since March this year, in Xian 
City 
proper, the authorities have seized a substantial amount of 
pirated audio-visual products, specifically, over 140,000 audio 
tapes and close to 100,000 video tapes. 

</TEXT>

