<F P=106> [By Debbie Kuo] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, June 22 (CNA) -- Guatemalan President 
Ramiro de Leon Carpio is slated to pay a state visit to the 
Republic of China [ROC] July 5-9, the Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs reported Wednesday [22 June]. 
  De Leon, who will be the first head of state from Latin 
America to visit Taiwan this year, is coming at the invitation 
of Premier Lien Chan, who called on De Leon in Guatemala in 
early June. 
  During his stay, De Leon will be bestowed with the Order of 
Brilliant Jade (Grand Cordon) by the ROC Government, in 
recognition of his contribution to strengthened relations 
between Guatemala and Taiwan. 
  He will exchange views with President Li Teng-hui on matters 
of mutual concern and international affairs. The two heads of 
state will also ink a communique confirming the solid friendship 
and cooperative ties between the two countries. 
  A staunch freedom fighter, De Leon last visited Taiwan three 
years ago as a delegate to captive week activities hosted by the 
World League for Freedom and Democracy, ROC chapter. 

