<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Air Force Delegation Departs Egypt for UAE </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Air Force Delegation Departs Egypt for UAE </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2206160294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1515 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206160294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, June 22 ( XINHUA)--A Chinese Airforce 
delegation led by Air Force commander General Cao Shuangming 
left here today for the United Arab Emirates [UAE] at the end of 
a week-long goodwill visit to Egypt. 
  During its stay here the delegation called on Marshal 
Muhammad Husayn Tantawi, Egyptian commander-in-chief of the 
armed forces and defense minister, General Ahmed Abdul Rahman 
Nimir [name as received], commander of Egypt's Air Force, and 
General Ahmed Abu Taleb [name as received], commander of Egypt's 
air defense forces. 
  The two sides held talks on strengthening friendship ties of 
cooperation between the two countries armed forces, particularly 
the air and air defense forces. 
  They also exchanged views on issues of mutual concern. 
  General Cao and his accompanying delegation arrived here on 
June 15 at an invitation from General Ahmed Abu Taleb, commander 
of the Egyptian air defense forces. 

</TEXT>

