<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qian Qichen Meets Former Public Functionaries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Qian Qichen Meets Former Public Functionaries </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Functionaries `Essential' to Operations </H4>

<F P=102> OW2306122694 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1036 
GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2306122694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Feng Xiuju (7458 4423 5468)] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 23 Jun (XINHUA) -- During his meeting with 
a delegation of the Association for Hong Kong's Former 
High-Ranking Public Functionaries in Beijing this afternoon, 
Vice Premier Qian Qichen said it is extremely important to have 
a stable contingent of public functionaries during Hong Kong's 
transition period. The delegation was led by Chen Naiqiang, 
Hong Kong's former secretary for lands and works. 
  Qian Qichen said: Public functionaries are essential in 
administrative operation. It is necessary to depend on public 
functionaries to ensure smooth take-over of sovereignty, stable 
transition, and the management of the Hong Kong Special 
Administrative Region after 1997. 
  He continued: The Sino-British Joint Statement and the Basic 
Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region have specific 
regulations concerning the continuing service of public 
functionaries. The purpose of these regulations is to maintain 
the stability of the rank-and-file of public functionaries. 
  Qian Qichen said: "The delegation's visit to Beijing is of 
great significance. We support your setting up the Association 
for Hong Kong's Former High-Ranking Public Functionaries." 
  He said: After Hong Kong returns to the motherland, those 
public functionaries who would like to stay and serve the Hong 
Kong Special Administrative Region and its residents are indeed 
patriotic people who love Hong Kong. 
  Qian Qichen expressed the hope that the contingent of public 
functionaries in Hong Kong will honestly perform their duties 
and serve the Hong Kong residents in the last few years of the 
transition period. 
  Qian Qichen emphatically said: As a financial, economic, and 
information center, Hong Kong is an economic-type city. It 
should focus on its administration and ensure high efficiency in 
its administrative management. 
  Lu Ping, director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office, 
was present during the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

