<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Burkina Faso President To Visit Taipei 18-22 Jul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Burkina Faso President To Visit Taipei 18-22 Jul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2306081794 Taipei CNA in English 0710 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2306081794 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Danielle Yang] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, June 23 (CNA) -- Burkina Faso President 
Blaise Compaore is scheduled to visit the Republic of China 
[ROC] July 18-22, the Foreign Ministry said Thursday [23 June]. 
  Burkina Faso resumed diplomatic relations with the ROC on 
February 2, 1994. 
  Compaore's visit is at the invitation of President Li 
Teng-hui. He will exchange views with Li on international 
situation and matters of mutual concern as well as visit local 
agricultural and economic establishments. 

</TEXT>

