<F P=100> REGIONAL ECONOMIC STATISTICAL COMMUNIQUES </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujian </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujian </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK0505083294 Fuzhou FUJIAN RIBAO in Chinese 8 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> HK0505083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Fuzhou FUJIAN RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by Fujian Provincial Statistics Bureau; </F>
date not given: "Statistical Report Issued by Fujian Provincial 
Statistics Bureau on National Economic and Social Development in 
1993"] 
  [Text] Under the leadership of the provincial party 
committee and government in 1993, the people of the whole 
province continued to implement the spirit of the 14th CPC 
Congress, earnestly enforced the measures of the CPC Central 
Committee and State Council on strengthening macroeconomic 
control and regulation, and maintained sustained, rapid, and 
healthy growth of the national economy. The comprehensive 
strength of the national economy was further enhanced, new 
strides were made in foreign economy and trade, the people's 
living standards continued to improve, and successes were made 
in science, technology, education, culture, public health, and 
other social undertakings. According to preliminary statistics, 
Gross Domestic Product totaled 95.349 billion yuan, an increase 
of 25.4 percent over 1992. Of this, added value in secondary 
industry totaled 44.632 billion yuan, up 41.8 percent, and 
tertiary industry reached 27.817 billion yuan, up 19.7 percent. 
Gross National Product was four times the figure in 1980, 
attaining the strategic objective of quadrupling national income 
seven years ahead of schedule. The main problems in economic 
operations included: Some state enterprises lacked vitality in 
their operations and production, the investment setup remained 
irrational, market prices rose sharply, and the development of 
basic industries and facilities could not meet the needs of 
rapid national economic growth. 
<H5>  1. Agriculture </H5>
  Agricultural production and the rural economy continued to 
grow. The added value of agriculture totaled 22.9 billion yuan, 
an increase of 7.5 percent over 1992. 
  The province speedily readjusted its crops. The sown area of 
grain was reduced, while that of cash crops was increased. 
Grain yields per unit area and output of edible oil, tobacco, 
fruit, and tea all reached all-time highs. 


------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
