|on hand                  |                         |                         | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Year-end number of cows  |4.6793 million head      |-1.4                     | 
|on hand                  |                         |                         | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


  Fisheries developed at a greater pace. Output of aquatic 
products in 1993 was 2.8075 million tonnes, up 11.8 percent over 
the previous year. Output of freshwater agricultural products 
increased by 18 percent, while that of saltwater agricultural 
products rose 7.5 percent. Progress was also made in tapping 
ocean resources in 1993. 
  Conditions for agricultural production improved. In late 
1993, power produced by farm machinery province-wide totaled 
16.1884 million kw, up 9.6 percent over same period last year; 
power consumption in the countryside came to 12.765 billion kwh, 
up 27.6 percent; fertilizers applied throughout 1993 amounted to 
1.6571 million tonnes (in terms of 100 percent active 
ingredients), down 6.6 percent from the previous year; and the 
area plowed by tractors stood at 787,900 hectares, down 12.1 
percent. 
  Township enterprises continued to grow at a high speed and 
their total income in 1993 amounted to 220 billion yuan, showing 
an increase of 48.9 percent compared with the previous year's 
figure. 
<H5>  2. Industry and Construction </H5>
  Industrial production increased considerably. The added 
value of industry was 126.4 billion yuan in 1993, up 36.6 
percent over the previous year, with the gross industrial output 
value hitting 508.845 billion yuan, up 36.5 percent. For 
industrial enterprises at county level and above, the output 
value of state enterprises increased 14.6 percent, collective 
enterprises 44.6 percent, and that of the other economic sectors 
with foreign-funded enterprises as the mainstay by 42.6 percent. 
Large and medium industrial enterprises made greater steps in 
transforming their managerial mechanisms, and their gross output 
value was up 23.7 percent over the previous year. 
  Light and heavy industries basically progressed 
simultaneously. The 1993 output value of light industry hit 
318.826 billion yuan, up 37.5 percent from the 1992 figure, 
while that of heavy industry reached 190.019 billion yuan, up 
34.5 percent. Affected by changing market needs, output of the 
principal industrial goods varied, with some rising and others 
falling. 
  Compared with the 1992 figures, the 1993 output of principal 
industrial goods was as follows: 


------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|1993 Output of Principal Industrial Goods Over 1992                          | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Bicycle                  |5.6590 million           |-4.4                     | 
