<F P=100> REGIONAL ECONOMIC STATISTICAL COMMUNIQUES </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangxi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guangxi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2004081894 Nanning GUANGXI RIBAO in Chinese 15 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> HK2004081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nanning GUANGXI RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the Guangxi Regional Statistics Bureau </F>
on 20 February 1994: "Statistical Report Issued by Guangxi 
Regional Statistics Bureau on National Economic and Social 
Development in 1993"] 
  [Text] In 1993, under the guidance of Comrade Deng 
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics and of the policies set out by the 14th party 
congress, all nationalities in Guangxi further emancipated their 
minds; seized the opportunity to accelerate the pace of reform, 
opening up, and economic construction; and conscientiously 
implemented various macroscopic measures formulated by the 
central authorities. On the basis of the previous year's 
high-speed growth, the regional national economy continued to 
develop in a healthy way while achieving political stability, 
unity of nationalities, and social progress. Moreover, new 
development was seen in various social undertakings, including 
the fields of economy, science and technology, education, 
culture, public health, and sports. Preliminary statistics 
indicated that the total value of GDP for the whole year was 
77.3 billion yuan, up 19.6 percent over the previous year. Of 
this total, the value added by primary industry was 26.078 
billion yuan, up 6.7 percent over the previous year; that of 
secondary industry hit 30.348 billion yuan, up 39.4 percent; and 
that of tertiary industry amounted to 20.839 billion yuan, up 
14.3 percent. The major problems that remained in economic 
performance were: shortage of funds, insufficient investment in 
agriculture, slow growth of peasants' real income, sluggish 
development of the communications and energy sectors, large 
increases in market prices, as well as poor efficiency and 
operational difficulties on the part of certain enterprises. 
<H5>  I. Agriculture </H5>
  In 1993, governments at all levels in our region 
conscientiously implemented the guidelines laid down by the 
central rural work meeting; enhanced leadership over 
agricultural production; fully engaged in the comprehensive 
development of agriculture; vigorously readjusted and optimized 
the internal structure of agriculture; vigorously popularized 
advanced agricultural technology; and took the path of high 
yields, fine quality, and high efficiency, thus achieving 
overall growth in agricultural production. Preliminary 
statistics indicated that the value added by the agricultural 
sector was 26.078 billion yuan, up 6.7 percent over the previous 
year, of which the planting industry, forestry, animal 
husbandry, and fisheries increased 1.7, 2.2, 17.4, and 24.7 
percent respectively. However, a number of outstanding problems 
remained, such as the relatively low economic benefit of 
agriculture, the slow growth of peasants' real income, the price 
scissors in the exchange of industrial products for agricultural 
products, and the ever-widening gap between incomes earned by 
urban and rural dwellers. 
  The planting industry developed in the midst of 
readjustment. 
As far as major farm produce was concerned, apart from a slight 
decrease in sugar cane yield due to a reduction in the growing 
area as compared with that of the previous year, grain yield was 
14.95 million tonnes, up 2.6 percent over the previous year, 
which once again hit historic highs. Moreover, an all-round 
bumper harvest was reaped in the yields of grain, soybeans, 
potatoes and the like, oil-bearing crops, tobacco, tea, and 
fruit. In addition, such crops as winter vegetables also 
achieved new development. 


