  New progress was made in forestry. The newly afforested area 
in 1993 covered 786,000 hectares (11.788 million mu), up 15.9 
percent over the previous year. The output of rosin reached 
245,000 tonnes, up 19.1 percent, and the output of tung tree 
seed reached 46,000 tonnes, up 2.1 percent, whereas the output 
of rapeseed was 66,000 tonnes, down 14.1 percent. 
  Huge growth was registered in animal husbandry and 
fisheries. 
Apart from steadily developing the production of pigs, various 
localities paid increasing attention to the production of 
grazing stock, poultry, and aquatic products, hence there were 
more pigs, oxen, sheep, and goats reared and slaughtered, making 
for tremendous growth in the total output of meat and aquatic 
products as compared with the previous year. The output of 
major products was as follows: 


