------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


  Further improvement was made in conditions for agricultural 
production. By the end of 1993, the aggregate power of farm 
machinery reached 93.91 billion Watts, a growth of 9.9 percent 
over the previous year-end figure. There were 12,400 large and 
medium-sized tractors, a drop of 2.4 percent; 19,500 trucks, up 
17.5 percent; irrigation and drainage equipment with a total 
power capacity of 930 million Watts, up 5.6 percent; and 1.4969 
million hectares with effective irrigation systems, a drop of 
1.1 percent. Moreover, a total of 1.0544 million tonnes of 
chemical fertilizers (100 percent effective content equivalent) 
were applied, registering an increase of 1.9 percent. Rural 
consumption of electricity was 1.898 billion kwh, up 11.8 
percent. 
  The rural economy continued to develop in a comprehensive 
way, and such nonagricultural economic sectors as rural 
industry, construction, transportation, trade, and catering grew 
by more than 100 percent over the previous year. Spurred by 
many positive factors, town and township enterprises maintained 
a trend of high-speed development, with the total income for the 
whole year reaching 73.569 billion yuan, up 140 percent over the 
previous year. The total amount of profits and taxes were 6.34 
billion yuan, up 110 percent over the previous year, of which 
4.457 billion yuan was the net profit and 1.883 billion yuan of 
state taxes were actually turned in, up 130 percent and 80.5 
percent, respectively, over the same period of the previous year. 
<H5>  II. Industry and Construction </H5>
  In 1993, reform of industrial enterprises was deepened and 
the enthusiasm of enterprises and their staff and workers was 
effectively aroused. Driven by a huge growth in demand for 
investment, industrial enterprises continued to maintain 
high-speed growth. The value added by industry for the whole 
year amounted to 26.255 billion yuan, up 40.5 percent over the 
previous year, and the proportion of the value added by industry 
to the total value of GDP rose from the previous year's 28.8 
percent to 33.9 percent. Regarding the value added by industry 
at and above the township level, which was calculated 
independently, that by state-owned enterprises was 1.598 billion 
yuan, up 33.6 percent, with the gradual enhancement of the 
market mechanism and the rapid development of non-state-owned 
enterprises, that by collective enterprises amounted to 3.61 
billion yuan, up 41.5 percent, and that by other economic types 
of enterprises (including foreign-funded enterprises) was 4.17 
billion yuan, up 47.7 percent. There are better links between 
production and marketing of industrial products, and the 
production-marketing rate of these products at and above the 
township level for the whole year reached 96.9 percent. 
  The growth of heavy industry is obviously faster than that 
of 
light industry, the proportion of the former to the latter rose, 
and the industrial structure was further readjusted. The value 
added by light industry at and above the township level, which 
was calculated independently, was 8.235 billion yuan, up 38.3 
percent over the previous year, and that by heavy industry was 
12.009 billion yuan, up 39.7 percent. Owing to the effect of 
greater demand for investment, there is, in general, huge growth 
in the output of capital goods, whereas the output of some of 
the unsalable goods dropped. 


------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Output of Major Industrial Products                                          | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|                         |1993                     |Percent Increase Over Pr-| 
|                         |                         |evious Year              | 
