------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Cargo handled at four po-|12.1427 million tonnes   |21.0                     | 
|rts                      |                         |                         | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


  Post and telecommunications services developed rapidly, with 
business transactions in 1993 totalling 780 million yuan, up 
69.81 percent over the previous year. Express mail service, 
paging, and mobile telephone service rose rapidly in various 
prefectures, cities, and counties. By the end of 1993, the 
number of urban telephone subscribers had reached 240,000, up 
52.7 percent over the previous year. Manual phones were no 
longer used in areas above the county and city levels throughout 
the region, and the process of urban telephone automation was 
completed, thus achieving the construction goal of the Eighth 
Five-Year Plan two years ahead of schedule. However, the 
communications capacity still could not meet the needs of social 
and economic development. In particular, communications in vast 
rural areas still were not smooth. 
<H5>  V. Domestic Trade and Market Prices </H5>
  The domestic market developed steadily, and institutional 
consumption was checked. With further acceleration in the pace 
of reform in circulation, the domestic market was flourishing, 
with brisk buying and selling, and there was an abundant supply 
of consumer goods. The total value of retail commodity sales 
was 34.276 billion yuan, up 25.2 percent over the previous year, 
or a real growth of 5.26 percent if price increases are 
deducted. Retail sales of consumer goods were 30.503 billion 
yuan, up 29.7 percent, and sales of means of production reached 
3.773 billion yuan, down 2.7 percent. Retail sales of consumer 
goods at urban markets were 13.881 billion yuan, up 43.1 percent 
over the previous year; sales in counties and cities were 7.606 
billion yuan, up 25.8 percent; and sales in villages were 9.016 
billion yuan, up 16.1 percent. In the latter half of 1993, 
owing to the implementation of state macroeconomic regulative 
measures, the growth rate of social institutional consumption 
apparently dropped. In 1993, retail sales of consumer goods 
sold to social institutions throughout the region were 1.857 
billion yuan, up 23.3 percent over the previous year, and the 
growth rate in the latter half of the year decreased by 13 
percent compared with the first half. 
  An overall increase was registered in retail sales of 
commodities by commercial units of all economic forms. Retail 
sales by state-owned units were 13.211 billion yuan, up 25.7 
percent over the previous year; sales by collective units were 
7.144 billion yuan, up 10.6 percent; and sales by supply and 
marketing cooperatives were 60 million yuan, up 29 percent; 
whereas the economy of individual units developed rapidly and 
their retail sales reached 1.0272 billion yuan, up 33.9 percent, 
which was the largest growth rate among all economic forms. 
Sales by peasants to nonagricultural residents were 3.590 
billion yuan, up 32.96 percent. Analyzed by the retail sales of 
all kinds of consumer goods, due to the effect of lifting 
restrictions on purchasing and selling prices of grain, retail 
sales of grain, pigs, and pork dropped slightly, whereas sales 
of other items rose to different degrees, of which the sales of 
edible vegetable oil increased 17.3 percent, sales of eggs 
increased 8.26 percent, sales of sugar increased 32.9 percent; 
most clothing items registered a growth, and the sales of cotton 
cloth and other garments increased 18.5 percent and 18.1 
percent, respectively. There was tremendous growth in sales of 
major consumer durables, of which sales of video recorders rose 
80.3 percent, sales of color TV sets rose 15.2 percent, sales of 
washing machines rose 53.1 percent, and sales of electric fans 
and household refrigerators increased by 33.0 percent and 20.2 
percent, respectively. 
  There was brisk buying and selling in the market for means 
of 
production. In 1993, the total purchase of means of production 
by material supply and marketing enterprises was 14.94 billion 
yuan, up 48.1 percent over the previous year, and the total 
amount of sales reached 15.24 billion yuan, up 42.3 percent. 
  The pace of price reform was accelerated, the market was 
more 
open, and the increase in commodity prices was quite high. Of 
the total volume of retail commodity sales throughout the 
region, commodities priced by the state accounted for only 5.4 
percent, the total amount of farm produce purchased accounted 
for merely 1.5 percent, and the total sales of industrial means 
of production accounted for 7.4 percent. In 1993, apart from 
relaxing restrictions on the purchasing and selling prices of 
grain, some commodity prices and service charges also were 
readjusted, thus bringing about a rise in price indices related 
to residents' cost of living. Consequently, there was quite a 
large rise in the general level of retail prices and of 
residents' cost of living. 
  The changes in prices in 1993, as compared with prices in 
the previous year, were as follows (the previous year's figures 
given as 100): 


------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|1. Index of residents' cost of living |122.0                                 | 
|prices                                |                                      | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
